TreeMap
Java ka TreeMap ek Map implementation hai jo data ko sorted order me store karta hai
— by default keys ke natural order me (jaise numbers ascending, strings alphabetical).
Ye internally Red-Black Tree use karta hai,
isliye operations (put, get, remove) generally O(log n) time lete hain.

Basic baat samajh le:
Duplicate keys allowed ❌
Values duplicate ho sakti hain ✅
Keys sorted rehte hain automatically ✅
Null key allowed nahi hoti ❌ (HashMap me hoti hai)

TreeMap ke “extra” methods
1. Navigation methods
Ye sorted nature ka fayda uthate hain:
firstKey() → sabse chhoti key
lastKey() → sabse badi key
higherKey(k) → given key se just badi key
lowerKey(k) → given key se just chhoti key
ceilingKey(k) → >= k
floorKey(k) → <= k

2. Entry-based navigation
Same cheez, par key + value dono ke saath:
firstEntry()
lastEntry()
higherEntry(k)
lowerEntry(k)
ceilingEntry(k)
floorEntry(k)

3. Range operations (bahut powerful)
subMap(fromKey, toKey) → ek range ka map
headMap(toKey) → chhoti keys ka part
tailMap(fromKey) → badi keys ka part

4. Reverse order
descendingMap() → ulta sorted map
descendingKeySet()

5.Poll methods (remove + return)
pollFirstEntry()
pollLastEntry()


